        "heading_axLTnn": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "<p>Morton’s Neuroma</p>",
            "heading_size": "title-md",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "highlighted_text": "text",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Morton’s Neuroma is a common foot condition characterized by pain, swelling, and inflammation of a nerve, typically located at the ball of the foot between the 3rd and 4th toes. Symptoms include sharp pain, burning sensations, and possibly a lack of feeling in the affected area, as well as tingling or cramping in the forefoot.<br/><br/>Footwear with pointed toes and/or high heels can contribute to Morton’s Neuroma, as constricting shoes can pinch the nerve between the toes, causing discomfort and extreme pain.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
            "text_capitalize": false,
